FBIS4-42813 "drweu110_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-110 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Berlusconi Calls For Rwanda Task Force Berlusconi Calls For Rwanda Task Force LD0706193794 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1745 GMT 7 Jun 94 LD0706193794 Rome RAI Due Television Network Italian BFN [Text] This morning, Silvio Berlusconi paid a visit to the Bambino Gesu hospital where 11 Rwandan children have been admitted. When asked about the possible solutions to the Rwandan tragedy, Berlusconi said: [Begin Berlusconi recording] I believe that if we have a true conscience as world citizens, then I believe we must find a way to intervene. We must find a way to intervene adequately, quickly, in an effective way; I believe that the world, those countries that are democratic and civilized, must find a way of setting up an army, a permanent task force for exactly this type of intervention. This task force could be made up perhaps of ordinary troops or volunteers. [end recording]
